    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen multiple LSP clients are attached to a buffer (e.g., `basedpyright` + `ty` + `ruff` for Python), `vim.lsp.buf.references()` / `definition()` / `declaration()` etc. return the **same result N times** (once per client) in the quickfix/location list.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Attach 2+ LSP clients that advertise `textDocument/references` (or `textDocument/definition`) to a Python buffer.\n2. Place cursor on any symbol.\n3. Run `:lua vim.lsp.buf.references()` or press `<leader>lR` (AstroNvim default).\n4. Quickfix window shows each reference duplicated N times (N = number of clients).\n\n### Root cause\n\n`get_locations()` in `runtime/lua/vim/lsp/buf.lua` queries all attached clients via `lsp.buf_request_all()` and blindly concatenates results:\n\n```lua\nfor client_id, res in pairs(results) do\n  local client = assert(lsp.get_client_by_id(client_id))\n  local locations = {}\n  if res then\n    locations = vim.islist(res.result) and res.result or { res.result }\n  end\n  local items = util.locations_to_items(locations, client.offset_encoding)\n  vim.list_extend(all_items, items)  -- <-- no deduplication\nend\n```\n\n[Permalink to source](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/7337e02563b5fbcc7ac8d50f127efa740fde38d6/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/buf.lua#L253-L261)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nResults displayed in quickfix should be deduplicated (by `filename:lnum:col`), similar to how completion items were deduplicated in PR #36166.\n\n### Precedent\n\nPR [#36166](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/36166) added deduplication for `textDocument/completion` results from multiple clients. The same pattern should apply to location-based results.\n\n### Affected functions\n\nAll LSP methods that go through `get_locations()`:\n- `vim.lsp.buf.references()`\n- `vim.lsp.buf.definition()`\n- `vim.lsp.buf.declaration()`\n- `vim.lsp.buf.type_definition()`\n- `vim.lsp.buf.implementation()`\n\n### Workaround (client-side)\n\nUsers currently work around this by overriding mappings with an `on_list` callback that deduplicates by `filename:lnum:col`:\n\n```lua\nvim.lsp.buf.references(nil, {\n  on_list = function(opts)\n    local seen, unique = {}, {}\n    for _, item in ipairs(opts.items) do\n      local key = (\"%s:%d:%d\"):format(item.filename, item.lnum, item.col)\n      if not seen[key] then seen[key] = true; unique[#unique + 1] = item end\n    end\n    opts.items = unique\n    vim.fn.setqflist({}, \" \", opts)\n    vim.cmd \"botright copen\"\n  end,\n})\n```\n\n### Additional note\n\n`vim.lsp.buf.format()` supports `filter`/`id`/`name` options to restrict which clients run, but `LocationOpts` / `ListOpts` do not. Adding client filtering to `get_locations()` would be an alternative (or complementary) fix.",
